SIMPLE: ingress
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ingress
<hw>In"gress</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ingressus</ets>, fr. <ets>ingredi</ets>. See
<er>Ingredient</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of entering; entrance; <as>as, the
<ex>ingress</ex> of air into the lungs</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Power or liberty of entrance or access; means of
entering; <as>as, all <ex>ingress</ex> was prohibited</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>The entrance of the moon into
the shadow of the earth in eclipses, the sun's entrance into a sign,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ingress</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ingress
<hw>In"gress</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To go in; to
enter.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ingression</ent>⟦br⟧
